<fanfic id="364">
<chapter>
<p>Faith was lying in a hospital room that the hospital seemed to have forgotten. It was fitting somehow, that a forgotten Slayer should lie in a forgotten room. She was comatose, but that didn't mean that her mind was blank. Oh no, her mind was active, very active. She wished she could stop it, but she couldn't.</p>
<p>Nightmarish images mixed with brief moments of serenity, which always turned into nightmares again. Buffy was present in most of those peaceful moments, and when they ended, she almost always ended up hurting Buffy. And the nightmares, they were her life. Her childhood, the death of her first Watcher, the betrayal by Gwendolyn Post, the murder of Allan Finch, her betrayal of Buffy and Buffy stabbing her. There were also images of something else, of something she didn't remember. Those last images scared her the most.</p>
<p>They were vague at first, but they were becoming more and more clear, and scary. Until she finally remembered.</p>
<p>Then her eyes fluttered open. She lay still for a few moments, confused, but then her memory returned and she remembered everything, except those last images. She looked around and saw she was in some storage room or something. She got up and wanted to leave, but the IV stopped her. She tore out the tubes and left the room.</p>
<p>She was walking down the hall when the doors at the end opened and a young woman came through. Faith was worried for a few moments, but she calmed down when she saw it was just a young woman.</p>
<p>"Excuse me," the woman spoke. "You know how to get to third floor west?"</p>
<p>"What?" Faith asked, confused.</p>
<p>"I see... You need some help or something?"</p>
<p>"Graduation."</p>
<p>"What?" the woman said, puzzled.</p>
<p>"Graduation. I gotta get to Sunnydale High School graduation. Now!"</p>
<p>"Well, you can't. I mean, Sunnydale High School isn't even there anymore"</p>
<p>Faith frowned.</p>
<p>"What day is it?"</p>
<p>"Friday."</p>
<p>"What date? The date?"</p>
<p>"February 25th."</p>
<p>"What year?"</p>
<p>The woman realized that Faith needed help.</p>
<p>"Maybe I should get you a nurse," she suggested.</p>
<p>"What happened to the school?"</p>
<p>"Don't you just wanna..."</p>
<p>"Just tell me," Faith said, agitated.</p>
<p>"Well, it was a tragedy, really. Lots of students died. The Principal, the Mayor." She paused for a moment. "I really think I should get you some help."</p>
<p>Faith stared at her. She was feeling this urge to beat up the woman and take her clothes. But then she got a flash of the hidden memories and she got scared.</p>
<p>"Are you okay?" the woman asked, concerned, when she saw Faith's face.</p>
<p>"Yeah, five by five," Faith said and hurried away before the impulse became too strong and she ended up beating the woman.</p>

<hr/>

<p>She ran down back alleys, avoiding people. She didn't know where to go, but then she finally decided to go back to the apartment the Mayor had bought her. She came across a few people and every time she felt the urge to beat them up and take their clothes. And every time, the memories became a bit clearer, and scarier. So she ran, as fast as she could.</p>

<hr/>

<p>Buffy and the Scoobs were at Giles' place discussing Adam when the phone rang. Giles answered it.</p>
<p>"Hello... What? Yes, she is." He motioned to Buffy. "Em, it's for you."</p>
<p>Buffy frowned, surprised, and went to the phone.</p>
<p>"Hello... What sort of emergency... No, I haven't... Thank you, I'll let you know."</p>
<p>"What is it?" Giles asked.</p>
<p>"It's Faith. She's awake. No one knows where she is."</p>
<p>"I'd say this qualifies for a "Worst Timing Ever" award," Xander said.</p>
<p>"What do we do?" Willow asked.</p>
<p>"Well, we have to find her," Giles said.</p>
<p>"What about Adam?"</p>
<p>"I'd hate to see the pursuit of a homicidal lunatic get in the way of pursuing a homicidal lunatic," Xander said.</p>
<p>"Well, Faith's not exactly low-profile girl," Buffy said, "I'll patrol and wait for her to make a move."</p>
<p>"But then what?" Giles asked.</p>
<p>"Ooh! I have an idea! Beat the crap out of her!" Willow said animatedly.</p>
<p>"Good plan," Xander agreed.</p>
<p>"Good on paper," Buffy said. "But we still have a decision to make. Do we hand her over to the cops? They wouldn't know what to do with a Slayer even if they knew we existed."</p>
<p>"What about the Council?" Willow asked.</p>
<p>"Been there, tried that," Xander said. "Not unlike smothering a forest fire with napalm as I recall."</p>
<p>"Well, the Initiative, they do have containment facilities," Giles suggested.</p>
<p>"One word: evil."</p>
<p>"There's no way around it," Buffy said. "Faith is back, and whether I like it or not, she's my responsibility."</p>
<p>"Yeah, too bad," Willow said."</p>
<p>"We have no idea where she is. We don't know what she's thinking, what she's feeling..."</p>
<p>"Who she's doing," Xander added.</p>
<p>"She could be terrified. Maybe she doesn't even remember. Or maybe she does and she's sorry and she's alone, hiding somewhere," Buffy said hopefully.</p>
<p>"Well, perhaps there's some form of rehabilitation we just haven't thought about," Giles said.</p>
<p>"And if not, ass-kicking makes a solid plan B," Willow said.</p>
<p>"I'm not going to rule it out," Buffy agreed. "First thing, we need to find her. Then we can take it from there."</p>
<p>"Who's Faith?" Riley asked innocently.</p>

<hr/>

<p>When after two days Faith still hasn't showed up, Buffy was getting worried, both about Faith and about what she might be up to. She talked to Spike, she talked to vamps, she talked to Willy, but no one had seen her. She even checked out all the bars and the motel, but Faith was not there. So finally, the only thing left was the apartment where they had last fought. She had hoped she wouldn't have to go there, but she didn't know where else to go.</p>
<p>She started feeling guilty all over again as she climbed the stairs. Everything was quiet. When she got to Faith's floor, she noticed that the door was slightly ajar. She carefully approached. She stopped for a moment when she reached the door. She took a deep breath and then peeked in. She didn't see Faith, but her senses were telling her that Faith was there. She gulped and slowly entered. She looked around, ready to fend off any attack. But when she saw Faith sitting by the bed, still wearing the hospital gown, hugging her knees, she stopped, surprised.</p>
<p>"Faith?" she asked, but Faith didn't respond.</p>
<p>Buffy hesitated for a moment and then went closer. She noticed that Faith's eyes were staring at nothing and that she was trembling.</p>
<p>"Faith," she called again.</p>
<p>Faith didn't respond and after a moment of hesitation kneeled beside her</p>
<p>"Faith," she said and gently shook her.</p>
<p>Faith jerked and her eyes focused. She looked at Buffy and when she realized who Buffy was, her eyes went wide. She backed off onto the bed and away from Buffy. Buffy could see it in her eyes that Faith was scared.</p>
<p>"I'm not gonna hurt you," she said and Faith laughed briefly, confusing Buffy.</p>
<p>"Stay away from me," Faith said.</p>
<p>"Faith..."</p>
<p>"Stay away!" Faith screamed when Buffy stepped closer.</p>
<p>"Okay, okay," Buffy said and took a step backwards.</p>
<p>Faith calmed a bit and backed off toward the wall. She took a few deep breaths to calm down. She gulped and ran her hand through her hair.</p>
<p>"What did they do to me?" she finally asked in a quiet voice.</p>
<p>Buffy frowned, puzzled.</p>
<p>"What do you mean?"</p>
<p>"They... They... did something to me," Faith said. "It hurt."</p>
<p>"Who?"</p>
<p>"They... I don't know... Doctors."</p>
<p>"Doctors?" Buffy said, confused. "They healed you. They..."</p>
<p>"No, not now, before."</p>
<p>"Before?"</p>
<p>"Before I came here. They did something," Faith said, trying to remember Then she looked at Buffy. "H-Help me," she said and a few tears slid down her cheeks. "P-Please."</p>
<p>The look in Faith's eyes scared Buffy, it was the same look she had seen in Angel's eyes when he came back from Hell. She took a deep breath, hoping that Faith wasn't acting.</p>
<p>"Can I come closer?"</p>
<p>Faith hesitated, uncertain, and then nodded.</p>
<p>"But be c-careful."</p>
<p>"Why?"</p>
<p>"B-Because I-I don't w-wanna hurt you."</p>
<p>"Why would you?" Buffy asked, puzzled, as she slowly approached Faith.</p>
<p>"I-I don't kn-know. S-some-t-time I get this u-urge to k-kill."</p>
<p>"Oh."</p>
<p>Faith hesitated for a moment.</p>
<p>"B-Buffy?"</p>
<p>"Yes?" Buffy said, surprised that Faith had used her whole name.</p>
<p>"I-I'm s-sorry," Faith said, looking down, ashamed, as a few more tears ran down her cheeks.</p>
<p>Buffy hesitated for a moment and then slowly reached out with her hand and lifted Faith's chin.</p>
<p>"Look at me," she said softly when Faith avoided looking into her eyes.</p>
<p>Faith gulped, hesitating, and then finally forced herself to look into Buffy's eyes. The look almost broke Buffy's heart.</p>
<p>"I'll help you," she said after a few moments and Faith breathed a sigh of relief.</p>
<p>"Th-Thank y-you," she said and Buffy realized that Faith was sincere.</p>
<p>"Do you have anything to wear?" she asked.</p>
<p>Faith looked at herself and realized she was still wearing the hospital gown.</p>
<p>"Oh." She looked up. "I-I think so."</p>
<p>She hesitated for a moment and then went to the closet. She rummaged through it and took out a set of clothes. She started to undress, but then remembered that Buffy was still there.</p>
<p>"Em, c-could you..."</p>
<p>Buffy realized what she meant and she found it... strange that Faith was suddenly so shy. She started to turn around when she realized that showing her back to Faith might not be the wisest idea.</p>
<p>"I-It's okay," Faith said, having guessed what was on Buffy's mind.</p>
<p>She turned around and started to take off the gown. Buffy hesitated for a moment, but then she turned, all the while listening to the sounds Faith was making.</p>
<p>Faith quickly dressed and when she turned around, she saw that Buffy had her back toward her.</p>
<p>"No," she said as she fought the urge to hurt Buffy.</p>
<p>"What?" Buffy said and turned, only to see Faith backing off.</p>
<p>"I-I'm ha-having this u-urge again," Faith said.</p>
<p>"Can you control it?"</p>
<p>Faith hesitated for a moment and then nodded.</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>Buffy thought about what to do next.</p>
<p>"Pack your stuff," she then said.</p>
<p>Faith frowned but did as she was told. The packing didn't take long and a couple of minutes later, she was ready. She looked at Buffy expectantly.</p>
<p>"Wh-Where are we going?" she asked anxiously.</p>
<p>Buffy hesitated for a moment.</p>
<p>"Home."</p>
<p>Faith's eyes went wide.</p>
<p>"Y-Your home?"</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>"A-Are you sure?" Faith asked and gulped. "I-I mean..."</p>
<p>"I'm sure," Buffy said. "Mom likes you and I know she'll want to help you."</p>
<p>"B-But what if can't c-control m-myself?"</p>
<p>"Scream and run away."</p>
<p>Faith thought about it.</p>
<p>"Okay," she finally said.</p>
<p>"Come."</p>
<p>Faith hesitated for a moment and then followed Buffy.</p>

<hr/>

<p>"Mom!" Buffy called when she and Faith came home.</p>
<p>"Yes, honey?" Joyce said as she came from the kitchen. "Faith," she said, surprised, to see the girl.</p>
<p>"Hi," Faith said nervously and looked down.</p>
<p>"Buffy?" Joyce asked.</p>
<p>"She wants my help," Buffy explained. "Can she stay here?"</p>
<p>Joyce looked at Faith, thinking.</p>
<p>"Do you want to stay here, Faith?" she asked.</p>
<p>Faith looked at her, surprised.</p>
<p>"I-I don't know. B-Buffy said I c-could," she said, glancing at Buffy.</p>
<p>"At least she wouldn't be alone, Mom," Buffy pleaded.</p>
<p>Joyce hesitated for a moment and then sighed.</p>
<p>"Okay."</p>
<p>"Thanks, Mom," Buffy said, relieved.</p>
<p>"Thank y-you," Faith said quietly.</p>
<p>"Come, let me show you to your room," Buffy said and led Faith upstairs. "Here," she said when the got to the room. "We'll have to change the sheets and... What's wrong?" she asked when she noticed that Faith's face had paled and that she was backing off. "Faith?"</p>
<p>Faith swallowed hard.</p>
<p>"While I was in c-coma, I-I had dream... We w-were changing sh-sheets and you... stabbed me. A-and when the Boss and I h-had a p-picnic, you chased me a-and I ended up... k-killing you."</p>
<p>"Oh," Buffy said, thinking. "Well, I'm not going to stab you, if that's what you're worried about."</p>
<p>Faith took a deep breath and forced herself to step into the room.</p>
<p>"We have another spare room," Buffy said.</p>
<p>Faith sighed and shook her head.</p>
<p>"It's okay," she said.</p>
<p>"You sure?"</p>
<p>Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"Yeah." She looked at Buffy. "Thanks."</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"Are you hungry?"</p>
<p>Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"Yeah."</p>
<p>"I'll tell Mom to make something."</p>
<p>"No, that's not necessary."</p>
<p>"You haven't eaten since you left the hospital."</p>
<p>"I-I..."</p>
<p>"You need food, Faith."</p>
<p>Faith sighed and nodded.</p>
<p>"Well, settle in. We'll change the sheets as soon as I get back."</p>
<p>Faith nodded and Buffy left. Faith looked around the room and then went to the bed and sat on it. The way the room looked just like in her dream was really freaky, but she decided to face her fear.</p>

<hr/>

<p>"Mom?" Buffy said as she entered the kitchen.</p>
<p>"Yes?"</p>
<p>"Faith hasn't eaten since she left the hospital. Can you make her something?"</p>
<p>"Sure." Joyce hesitated for a moment. "How is she?"</p>
<p>Buffy thought about it.</p>
<p>"She's scared. She believes some doctors did something to her."</p>
<p>"Really?"</p>
<p>"Yes. But she can't remember what it was." She hesitated for a moment. "She even apologized."</p>
<p>"That's good, isn't it?"</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"Yes." She sighed. "Damn, we still have to take care of the police."</p>
<p>"What will you do about it?"</p>
<p>Buffy took a deep breath.</p>
<p>"I don't know. I'll have to talk to the guys."</p>
<p>"Do they know about Faith?"</p>
<p>"No, we came straight here." She hesitated for a moment. "I'm worried about how Willow and Xander will react to it, they're not very fond of her."</p>
<p>"Maybe you should talk to them before they meet her," Joyce suggested.</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"Yeah. I'll go to Giles' place later. We'll change the sheets in Faith's room now."</p>
<p>"Okay, honey."</p>

<hr/>

<p>As they changed the sheets, Buffy made sure she wasn't too close to Faith, not only because she still didn't completely trust her, but she also didn't want to make Faith jumpy.</p>
<p>"I'll go tell the guys later," she said as they finished.</p>
<p>Faith looked at her and nodded.</p>
<p>"You okay with that?" Buffy asked.</p>
<p>"Yeah, they h-have to find out." She hesitated for a moment. "How do y-you think they'll r-react?"</p>
<p>"I don't know. I think Willow and Xander will the most upset."</p>
<p>Faith frowned.</p>
<p>"Why?"</p>
<p>Buffy shrugged.</p>
<p>"I don't know. They're afraid of you, I guess."</p>
<p>"Oh." She thought for a moment. "Do... Do you know where h-he's buried?"</p>
<p>"He? Finch."</p>
<p>Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"No, I don't."</p>
<p>"Oh."</p>
<p>"I'll find out," she said and Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"Okay." She hesitated for a moment. "A-And P-Professor W-Wirth."</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"Him too." She thought for a moment. "Are you gonna be okay alone with my mom?"</p>
<p>Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"Yeah, I guess so."</p>
<p>"Okay."</p>

<hr/>

<p>"Have you found her yet?" Xander asked when Buffy came to Giles' place.</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>"You have?" Xander said, surprised. "Where is she? What happened?"</p>
<p>"She's at my place."</p>
<p>There was silence.</p>
<p>"Did you just say she was at your place?"</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>"Oh. I thought... She's at your place?!"</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>"In chains, I assume."</p>
<p>"No."</p>
<p>"What do you mean, no?"</p>
<p>"She's not in chains." Buffy looked at Giles. "Is it possible that the Council did something to her?"</p>
<p>"Like what?"</p>
<p>"I don't know. She was pretty scared when I found her. She said some doctors did something to her before she came here."</p>
<p>"And you assume it's the Council?"</p>
<p>"I wouldn't put it past them."</p>
<p>Giles thought for a moment.</p>
<p>"I don't know. And I don't think it would be wise to ask until we know more."</p>
<p>"So you left Faith alone in your house?" Willow asked.</p>
<p>"No, she's with Mom."</p>
<p>"You left her alone with your mom?! Buffy, she's dangerous! She..."</p>
<p>"She's sorry."</p>
<p>"What?"</p>
<p>"She said she was sorry."</p>
<p>"And you believe her?"</p>
<p>"Yes. She was terrified, I could see it in her eyes. And she asked me to help her."</p>
<p>"And you said yes?" Xander asked.</p>
<p>"Yes," Buffy said, getting slightly annoyed.</p>
<p>"But she..."</p>
<p>"I know what she did, Willow," Buffy interrupted her, "you don't have to remind me."</p>
<p>"Are you sure she is sincere?" Giles asked.</p>
<p>"Yes. Look, I know she's a good actress, but this time she was sincere. Whatever happened to her is scaring her."</p>
<p>"And she has no idea what?"</p>
<p>"No."</p>
<p>"How convenient," Xander said.</p>
<p>"Look, just give her a chance, okay? What if it is true? If the Council did something to her, they could do the same to me."</p>
<p>"She d-does have a p-point," Tara said and Willow looked at her, surprised.</p>
<p>"See?" Buffy said. "And what if she has really changed? We could use another Slayer when we go against Adam."</p>
<p>"And what if she hasn't?" Willow said.</p>
<p>"Yeah, what if she comes after us?" Xander added.</p>
<p>"She won't."</p>
<p>"You don't know that."</p>
<p>"I do." She sighed. "Look, I'll make a quick patrol and then I'm gonna go home." She looked at Giles. "I'll let you know how it goes."</p>
<p>Giles nodded.</p>
<p>"Okay."</p>
<p>"Good. I'll see you around."</p>

<hr/>

<p>After Buffy had left, Faith was at a loss as to what to do. She went to her room and stayed there for a while, but then she got bored and she went downstairs. Joyce was in the kitchen and she didn't really feel like talking to her. So she sat on the sofa and turned on the TV. Joyce came to check out the noise a few moments later and Faith got worried for a moment, but Joyce just smiled when she saw her, and returned to the kitchen. Faith heaved a sigh of relief and returned to watching TV.</p>
<p>But, unfortunately, most of the things on TV caused bad memories for her, either an action movie, a CNN update on some war, a medical show or even a cartoon. The flashbacks returned and Faith found herself in a loop of painful memories.</p>
<p>When Joyce left the kitchen a few minutes later, she found Faith staring at the TV, trembling.</p>
<p>"Faith?" she asked, but Faith didn't respond. "Faith, are you okay?" she asked again, concerned, and stepped closer.</p>
<p>Faith didn't respond, so Joyce slowly approached her. She noticed that Faith's hands were balled into fists and that her eyes were staring at nothing. She hesitated for a moment and then gently shook Faith.</p>
<p>"Faith..."</p>
<p>Faith shrieked and backed off from the startled Joyce. It took her a few moments to realize where she was and who Joyce was.</p>
<p>"S-Sorry," she mumbled and looked away.</p>
<p>Joyce slowly approached her and Faith tensed.</p>
<p>"Are you okay?" she asked.</p>
<p>"F-Five by f-five," Faith said, avoiding Joyce's eyes.</p>
<p>"Faith."</p>
<p>Faith gulped and forced herself to look at Joyce.</p>
<p>"It's okay," Joyce said. "You're hurt, you don't have to pretend that you're not," she said and smiled softly. "It's okay to cry," she added.</p>
<p>Faith touched her cheeks and saw that they were wet. Then she noticed the blood on her hands and she started shaking again.</p>
<p>"Oh my god, you're bleeding," Joyce said, having also noticed the blood. "Faith?" she said, noticing that Faith was trembling.</p>
<p>She gently touched Faith's shoulder again and Faith jerked.</p>
<p>"I didn't mean it! It was an accident!" she screamed.</p>
<p>"Faith, it's okay," Joyce said and covered Faith's hands. "Faith, look at me."</p>
<p>Faith did and Joyce was shocked by the look in her eyes.</p>
<p>"It was an accident," she said and Faith nodded. "Come, let's go take care of your hands."</p>
<p>She let go of Faith's hands and got up. Faith hesitated for a moment and then got up as well. Joyce started for the stairs and Faith slowly followed her.</p>
<p>"Wash your hands," Joyce said when they got to the bathroom.</p>
<p>Faith hesitated for a moment and then approached the sink and washed the blood off her hands. Joyce then looked at her palms, where the wounds from Faith's nails were already healing.</p>
<p>"Do you want me to put on a bandage?" she asked.</p>
<p>Faith shook her head.</p>
<p>"No, it's okay," she said in a raspy voice.</p>
<p>"Are you sure?"</p>
<p>Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"Yeah, they've already healed."</p>
<p>"Okay." Joyce hesitated for a moment. "Do you want to talk about it?"</p>
<p>Faith gulped and looked away, nervous.</p>
<p>"About what?"</p>
<p>"I don't know, whatever you want."</p>
<p>Faith took a deep breath to calm down a bit.</p>
<p>"No, not yet," she said.</p>
<p>"Okay. If you change your mind, don't hesitate to ask."</p>
<p>Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"Okay."</p>
<p>Joyce smiled a bit and then turned to leave.</p>
<p>"Mrs S-Summers?" Faith called after her.</p>
<p>Joyce turned back.</p>
<p>"Yes?"</p>
<p>Faith hesitated for a moment, gulping.</p>
<p>"Th-Thanks."</p>
<p>Joyce smiled.</p>
<p>"You're welcome," she said and left.</p>
<p>Faith closed her eyes and sighed. Then she looked at the mirror. She felt like smashing it, but she controlled herself and quickly left.</p>

<hr/>

<p>When Buffy came home, she went to her mother, who was in the living room</p>
<p>"Mom?"</p>
<p>Joyce looked at her with a smile.</p>
<p>"Hi, honey."</p>
<p>"Where's Faith?"</p>
<p>"She's taking a shower."</p>
<p>"Oh. Was everything okay?"</p>
<p>"Most of the time."</p>
<p>"What do you mean?" Buffy asked, worried.</p>
<p>"Well, I found her here, staring at nothing, and when I touched her, she... freaked. She was scared. And when she saw the blood on her hands, she... zoned out again."</p>
<p>"Blood? What blood?"</p>
<p>"She dug her nails into her palms."</p>
<p>"Oh."</p>
<p>"She calmed down, but I'm worried that she might have a nightmare tonight."</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"I'll leave my door open."</p>

<hr/>

<p>After Faith was finished showering, she went to her room. Buffy considered talking to her right away, but she decided to shower first. When she was done, she dressed into her sleeping clothes and went to Faith's room. She knocked, but there was no response.</p>
<p>"Faith?" she said and knocked again.</p>
<p>There was no response, so she slowly opened the door and peeked in.</p>
<p>"Faith?" she said when she saw Faith sitting on the bed, hugging her knees. "Faith!" she called.</p>
<p>Faith jerked and looked at her and Buffy could see that she had been going down the memory lane again.</p>
<p>"You okay?" Buffy asked.</p>
<p>"F-Five... No," Faith said.</p>
<p>"May I come in?"</p>
<p>Faith frowned first, surprised that Buffy was asking for her permission, and then nodded. Buffy entered the room and approached the bed. She hesitated for a moment and then sat down.</p>
<p>"Wanna talk about it?" she asked.</p>
<p>Faith sighed and hugged her knees tighter. She leaned her head on her knees and thought about the offer.</p>
<p>"I-I don't know what to s-say," she finally said, avoiding Buffy's eyes. "I m-mean, you were trying to be there for m-me and I screwed you over and b-betrayed you. And I'm still not s-sure why. I didn't want to, b-but... I don't know." She thought for a moment. "I kept having a feeling that I should... hurt you, but I didn't want to. But I did. A-And while I was in coma, I kept having these memory flashes, but when I woke up, I couldn't remember anymore." She sighed. "All I know is that someone did something to me." She gulped. "And every time I start to remember, I just... freak. I'm tired, but I'm afraid to go to sleep, because I know I'll either dream of what they did to me or of what I did."</p>
<p>Buffy stared at her for a few moments.</p>
<p>"Do you want me to stay here overnight?"</p>
<p>Faith looked at her pleadingly.</p>
<p>"Would you?" she asked in a small voice.</p>
<p>"If you want."</p>
<p>Faith hesitated for a moment and then nodded.</p>
<p>"Yes. Please."</p>
<p>Buffy was surprised by Faith's pleading tone, not being used to it, but she didn't comment.</p>
<p>"Okay," she said.</p>
<p>"Thank you," Faith said quietly and looked away again, not used to asking for help or thanking for it.</p>
<p>"I've talked to the guys," Buffy said and Faith looked at her anxiously.</p>
<p>"Wh-What did they say?"</p>
<p>"Well, Willow and Xander had the most to say. They don't trust you and they're afraid of you."</p>
<p>"Oh," Faith said and looked away.</p>
<p>Buffy hesitated for a moment and then touched Faith's hand, causing Faith to look at her.</p>
<p>"Don't worry, once they see that you've... well, that you are not a psycho, they'll start feeling more comfortable around you."</p>
<p>Faith stared at Buffy for a few moments, thinking.</p>
<p>"Why are you helping me?" she then asked.</p>
<p> Buffy sighed.</p>
<p>"I don't know. I guess I feel responsible for what happened to you. I mean, I was also there when you killed Finch, but we blamed you like you were the only one responsible for his death. And I guess we could've included you more in our lives, you must've felt like an outsider," she said and Faith nodded absentmindedly. "It's gonna be hard for you for a while, but I promise I'll be there for you, Faith. And if you wanna talk to me, don't be afraid to say so, okay?"</p>
<p>Faith nodded.</p>
<p>"So, em, you wanna talk about something else? I mean, I can bring you up to date on what's been going on since I... stabbed you."</p>
<p>Faith thought for a moment and then nodded.</p>
<p>"Okay."</p>
<p>Buffy hesitated for a moment.</p>
<p>"I'm sorry, you know. I know I was pissed, but I had no right to stab you."</p>
<p>"I understand," Faith said and Buffy smiled a little. She gulped. "But I wanted you to."</p>
<p>"What?" Buffy asked, puzzled.</p>
<p>"I w-wanted to you e-end it for m-me," Faith explained.</p>
<p>"Oh," Buffy said, surprised. She took a deep breath. "So, em, can I sit beside you?"</p>
<p>Faith hesitated for a moment and then moved a bit so Buffy could sit beside her.</p>
<p>"Thanks. Okay now, let's see..."</p>

<hr/>

<p>When Faith fell asleep, Buffy covered her with a blanket. She observed at her for a while, thinking she looked so innocent. Then she considered going to her room, but she decided to stay, in case Faith had a nightmare.</p>

<hr/>

<p>In the middle of the night, Buffy was awoken by sounds and movement. She listened for a moment, ready to fight, but then she realized it was Faith whimpering. She turned on the light and faced her. She saw that Faith was crying in sleep and that she was obviously scared. She gently shook her.</p>
<p>"Faith."</p>
<p>Faith opened her eyes with a yelp.</p>
<p>"It's okay," Buffy said and Faith looked at her, wide-eyed.</p>
<p>Faith looked away and quickly wiped her eyes, embarrassed.</p>
<p>"It's okay to cry, Faith," Buffy said, touching Faith's shoulder again.</p>
<p>Faith sobbed for a few moments and then calmed down.</p>
<p>They lay quietly for a while, Buffy making sure Faith drifted off to sleep first.</p>

<hr/>

<p>During the next few days, Faith stayed at home and the Scoobs avoided the house like it contained a plague. Joyce offered to stay as well, to keep her company, but Faith told her it was okay for her to go to work. But those hours that she was alone proved to be a hard trial for Faith, who had nothing to distract herself with but TV, radio and newspapers. She read the newspapers, listened to radio and watched TV, but it only took a little thing to bring back the bad memories. Sometimes it took her only a few minutes to break out of her reverie, but sometimes, it took her an hour or more. And each time it was over, she wanted to scream and beat something or someone up to relieve the pain. But she held herself in check.</p>
<p>For a day. Then she decided that the only thing she could hurt was herself. She got a knife and went to the bathroom. She took off her shirt and slowly started to cut gashes across her upper arm, one day on the left arm, the next on the right one. After only took three or four gashes, relief washed over her and the tears came. She let them flow for a while. Then she cleaned up the knife, her arms, which were already healing, and the floor. She dressed up, took the knife back into the kitchen, and watched some TV again.</p>
<p>Buffy volunteered to stay with Faith each night and Faith accepted, relieved to know that when the nightmare came, someone would be there to wake her up and comfort her. She was a bit uncomfortable at first because that someone was Buffy, but she quickly got used to it. In the morning, she was embarrassed at first, but she quickly relaxed when Buffy didn't make a big deal out of it.</p>
<p>Then, one night, Faith had a particularly bad nightmare and she was tossing and turning and screaming. It took Buffy a few moments to wake her up.</p>
<p>"No!" Faith screamed as she instinctively pushed Buffy away.</p>
<p>Buffy caught herself before she fell off the bed.</p>
<p>"Faith, it's me, it's okay."</p>
<p>Faith's teary eyes finally focused and she looked at her, puzzled.</p>
<p>"You had a nightmare," Buffy explained. "Do you remember anything?"</p>
<p>Faith sat up, pulling her knees to her body, hugging them. She thought for a few moments and then nodded.</p>
<p>"Th-They b-brain-w-washed m-me, I-I think." She frowned as she tried to remember. "...the b-best... o-obey... kill... B-Buffy... No! H-Have to k-kill... No! D-Don't w-wanna... "Kill... kill... kill... Obey... No!"</p>
<p>Faith started to tremble again, like she was talking to someone who wasn't there. Buffy quickly hugged her.</p>
<p>"It's okay, Faith, it's okay," she said, caressing her.</p>
<p>"I-I'm scared," Faith whimpered, crying, and hugged her back.</p>
<p>"Me to," Buffy whispered.</p>
<p>"Don't wanna kill. You."</p>
<p>"I know."</p>
<p>"I-I'm l-losing it."</p>
<p>"Shhh," Buffy tried to comfort her, tears running down her cheeks.</p>
<p>Faith slowly drifted off to sleep, hugging Buffy tightly, afraid to wake up alone. Buffy quietly held her, wondering if the Council had brainwashed Faith.</p>

<hr/>

<p>Buffy was the first to wake up in the morning. She was a bit puzzled to find herself hugging Faith and vice versa, but then she remembered the previous night and she relaxed. She caressed Faith, wondering what to do to help her, and Faith snuggled even closer, as if she was instinctively feeling that she was safe in Buffy's arms.</p>
<p>When Faith finally woke up, she was startled at first to find herself in Buffy's arms, and she pulled back.</p>
<p>"I-I'm s-sorry," she said, worried that she had somehow insulted Buffy.</p>
<p>Buffy smiled.</p>
<p>"It's okay."</p>
<p>Faith glanced at the clock.</p>
<p>"D-Don't you have s-school today?"</p>
<p>"Not for another hour."</p>
<p>Faith frowned.</p>
<p>"Oh."</p>
<p>Buffy hesitated for a moment.</p>
<p>"Do you remember anything from last night?"</p>
<p>Faith seemed to shrink as she shook her head.</p>
<p>"N-No, o-only... feelings."</p>
<p>"Oh." Buffy thought for a moment. "I'll ask Giles if he could hypnotize you. If you want."</p>
<p>Faith thought for a moment.</p>
<p>"I-I don't kn-know," she said uncertainly. "I-I'm scared," she added, whispering.</p>
<p>"I'll be there with you, if you want."</p>
<p>Faith gulped and then took a deep breath.</p>
<p>"O-Okay," she said and Buffy smiled at her.</p>
<p>"Okay, I'll ask Giles," Buffy said and Faith nodded. Buffy got up. "Feeling better?" she asked.</p>
<p>Faith smiled for a brief moment.</p>
<p>"Yeah. Th-Thanks."</p>
<p>Buffy smiled.</p>
<p>"No problem," she said and left.</p>
<p>Faith lay back and stared at the ceiling. She had lied to Buffy, she did remember one thing. <i>Kill Buffy.</i> She shuddered, fighting the voice in her head. She would not kill Buffy. Or anyone else. Except maybe herself, if that was what it would take not to kill someone else.</p>

<hr/>

<p>In the evening, Faith heard the scream and she ran to the door. She saw Joyce fighting a vamp and she ran out to protect her. She pushed the vamp away and then started to beat him instead of staking him. She knew what the vamp was and she wanted to take out her frustration on him.</p>
<p>Joyce stared at Faith for a few moments as Faith beat up the vamp, and then decided to intervene.</p>
<p>"Faith," she said, but Faith didn't respond. She went closer. "Faith," she called again, but Faith continued to ignore her. "Faith," she said and put her hand on Faith's shoulder.</p>
<p>Faith reacted by hitting her. Joyce stumbled away, realizing that touching Faith while she was out of her mind was not the smartest thing to do. Faith then she realized what she has done and she stared at Joyce, shocked.</p>
<p>"I-I'm s-sorry, I-I d-didn't m-mean it," Faith stuttered as a few tears rolled down her cheek.</p>
<p>"I know," Joyce said. Then her eyes went wide as she noticed another vampire running at Faith at full speed. "Faith..."</p>
<p>Faith saw the warning in Joyce's eyes just a little too late. She started to turn, but the vamp was upon her and he knocked her out. Joyce gasped as the vamp buried his fangs into Faith's neck and started to drink. She hesitated for a moment and then ran toward him and kicked him in the head. The vamp fell off Faith and touched his head, dizzy. Then he recovered and looked at Joyce. Joyce gulped and looked around for a stake. Unfortunately, Faith didn't bring a stake with her.</p>

<hr/>

<p>Buffy was returning from Giles' place when she saw the commotion in front of her house. She started running and her heart started to beat faster when she saw her mother fighting a vamp. Then she got closer and she saw that Faith and another vamp were lying on the ground, unconscious. She ran as fast as she could, her stake ready.</p>
<p>"Buffy!" Joyce called, having noticed her.</p>
<p>The vamp turned and prepared to defend himself, but Buffy plowed through his defenses and staked him.</p>
<p>"Mom?" Buffy asked and looked at Faith.</p>
<p>"I'm fine, honey," Joyce said and Buffy moved to Faith. "He hit her on the head and started drinking," Joyce explained.</p>
<p>Buffy kneeled beside Faith, stabbed the unconscious vamp and put the stake away. She checked Faith's heartbeat and then gently examined Faith's wound. She was relieved that it wasn't too torn. She picked her up and carried her up to the bathroom.</p>
<p>There, she took care of the bite wound, which was already healing. Then she removed the torn and bloody shirt and her eyes went wide when she noticed the scars on Faith's arms, which had obviously been reopened many times. She stared at them, puzzled at first, but then she realized that Faith must have cut herself. She stared at Faith, shocked and confused.</p>
<p>She finally took a deep breath and threw the torn shirt to the bin. She was about to pick up Faith, when Faith woke up.</p>
<p>"Faith?"</p>
<p>Faith looked around, puzzled.</p>
<p>"What..." She trailed off when she realized that she wasn't wearing a shirt and that Buffy could see the cuts on her upper arms. She immediately covered them, even though it was too late. "H-How's your mom?"</p>
<p>"She's fine," Buffy said. "Why did you cut yourself?"</p>
<p>Faith seemed to shrink and she looked away, embarrassed. Buffy gently touched her and Faith looked at her for a moment.</p>
<p>"S-So I w-wouldn't h-hurt som-meone else," she said quietly and hugged her knees.</p>
<p>"Oh Faith," Buffy said and wanted to hug her, but Faith quickly got up and ran to her room.</p>
<p>Buffy sighed and got up.</p>
<p>"Honey?" Joyce asked when she came out of the bathroom.</p>
<p>Buffy looked at her.</p>
<p>"She cut herself."</p>
<p>Joyce frowned.</p>
<p>"What do you mean?" she asked and came closer.</p>
<p>"She cut her upper arms."</p>
<p>"Why?"</p>
<p>Buffy sighed.</p>
<p>"She said that because she didn't want to hurt someone else."</p>
<p>"So she hurt herself instead."</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"Yes. I'm worried, Mom."</p>
<p>"Did you talk to Mr Giles?"</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"Yeah. I was gonna take Faith there now, but she's too upset and scared. I'll tell him we'll come tomorrow, or whenever Faith's ready."</p>
<p>Joyce nodded and hugged her. Buffy hugged her back and they stood like that for a few moments.</p>

<hr/>

<p>In her room, Faith was sitting on her bed, hugging her knees, shaking. She was crying, terrified. She was losing it and she knew it. It was only a matter of time before she lost it completely, and when she did, cutting herself would no longer be enough. She considered killing herself, but there was still hope there that Buffy would somehow help her.</p>
<p>When she heard Buffy going downstairs with Joyce, Faith made her decision. She quickly put on another shirt and went to the door. She listened for a few moments and when she heard that Buffy was on the phone, she opened the window, climbed down and disappeared into the night.</p>

<hr/>

<p>When Buffy came up a few minutes later, she went to Faith's room and gently knocked. There was no response, so she slowly opened the door.</p>
<p>"Faith?" she said before she peeked in.</p>
<p>She frowned when she didn't see her. But then she noticed that the window was open and she got a bad feeling.</p>
<p>"Faith?" she said and ran to the window.</p>
<p>She looked out, but Faith was nowhere to be seen. She ran out of the room.</p>
<p>"Faith!" she called and went from room to room, but Faith was not there.</p>
<p>She ran downstairs.</p>
<p>"What's wrong, honey?" Joyce asked, concerned.</p>
<p>"Faith, she's gone."</p>
<p>"What? Why?"</p>
<p>"I don't know. I'm gonna go look for her."</p>
<p>"Okay, honey. Be careful."</p>
<p>"I will," Buffy said and ran out.</p>

<hr/>

<p>"Anything?" Giles asked when Buffy came to him the next evening.</p>
<p>Buffy sighed, shaking her head.</p>
<p>"No."</p>
<p>"Buffy."</p>
<p>Buffy jerked, startled, and looked at Riley.</p>
<p>"Hi," she said, smiling a little.</p>
<p>Riley came closer.</p>
<p>"Are you okay?" he asked.</p>
<p>"Yeah," she said and him. "But I'm worried about Faith."</p>
<p>"Em, you said she started to remember?" Giles said.</p>
<p>Buffy let go of Riley and looked at Giles.</p>
<p>"Yes. Someone was telling her to obey and to kill me."</p>
<p>"Kill you?" Giles said, alarmed.</p>
<p>"Yes. She didn't remember in the morning."</p>
<p>"Oh."</p>
<p>"Are you sure she isn't just crazy?" Xander asked.</p>
<p>Buffy glared at him.</p>
<p>"No. Someone did something to her, brainwashed her, I think." She looked at Giles. "And for some reason she's remembering. Partly, anyway." She sighed. "I'm gonna go look for her."</p>
<p>"Do you want me to come along?" Riley asked.</p>
<p>Buffy thought for a moment.</p>
<p>"No, I think it would be better if we split. That way we could search a wider area."</p>
<p>"I don't know what she looks like," Riley pointed out.</p>
<p>Buffy frowned.</p>
<p>"Oh." She sighed. "Okay then." She looked at Willow and Xander. "Are you guys coming?"</p>
<p>Willow and Xander looked at one another.</p>
<p>"Em, we're not as sure about her as you are," Willow then said.</p>
<p>Buffy nodded.</p>
<p>"Okay," she said. "I'll see you later."</p>
<p>She and Riley left and Willow and Xander looked at one another, feeling bad for letting Buffy down.</p>

<hr/>

<p>As Buffy and Riley walked around Sunnydale searching for Faith, Riley observed Buffy.</p>
<p>"Are you okay?" he finally asked.</p>
<p>Buffy looked at him, startled.</p>
<p>"What? Oh. Yeah." She sighed and started to look around again. "I'm just worried about Faith. She... She's so... fragile, you know?"</p>
<p>"I thought she was your enemy."</p>
<p>Buffy glanced at him.</p>
<p>"So did I. But she's not. I think it was just her conditioning breaking through."</p>
<p>"Conditioning?" Riley asked, puzzled.</p>
<p>"I think she's been brainwashed."</p>
<p>"By whom?"</p>
<p>"The Council."</p>
<p>Riley frowned.</p>
<p>"Why would the Council brainwash her?"</p>
<p>Buffy sighed.</p>
<p>"I don't know."</p>

<hr/>

<p>At the mansion, Faith was raving. Again. She had chained herself to the wall and was now trying to escape her prison. But the chains held. Her clothes were bloody and she was sitting in a pool of her own blood, which had come from numerous cuts all over her body. Near by was a piece of glass which she had used to cut herself. She took the piece of glass and ran it across her face, leaving a nasty gash in its wake. When she ran out of face, she ran the glass down her neck, past her breasts and stopped when she reached her legs. The mental pain momentarily gone, she pulled her legs to her chest and cried for a while.</p>
<p>When she calmed down a bit, she realized she was still holding the piece of glass. She looked at it and saw the blood on her hands. She dropped the piece of glass and the bad memories came back again. She zoned out for a while, lost in the world of her confusing memories, and then started to rave all over again, until she was exhausted and Morpheus took her into the land of nightmares.</p>

<hr/>

<p>Spike was returning to his crypt from the shopping trip to the city dump when he noticed suspicious movement. Thinking it was the Initiative soldiers, he quickly hid. It didn't take long before three men came by. Spike was about to move on when he heard that the men were talking with British accent. He quickly realized that they were from the Watchers' Council. He waited until they were gone and then went to find Buffy. After, of course, he dropped his stuff off at the crypt, since there were a few items that he didn't want Buffy to see.</p>

<hr/>

<p>"Isn't it a little too late for a date?" Spike asked when he approached Buffy and Riley, who were still searching for Faith.</p>
<p>Buffy glared at him.</p>
<p>"What do you want, Spike?"</p>
<p>"Nothing."</p>
<p>"Then why are you here?"</p>
<p>"Oh, I just came across an interesting piece of news."</p>
<p>"And that is?"</p>
<p>"The Watchers are in town."</p>
<p>Buffy frowned.</p>
<p>"What do you mean?"</p>
<p>Spike rolled his eyes.</p>
<p>"What I said. There's three of them and they're looking for something. Or someone."</p>
<p>Buffy's eyes went wide.</p>
<p>"Faith."</p>
<p>"The Slayer?" Spike asked.</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>"Isn't she in the hospital where you put her?"</p>
<p>Buffy glared at him again.</p>
<p>"No. Right now, we don't know where she is."</p>
<p>"And they want her?"</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>"Why?"</p>
<p>"What do you think?"</p>
<p>"They want to off her because she's crazy?"</p>
<p>Buffy grabbed Spike by the throat.</p>
<p>"She's not crazy," she said and pushed him away. "They brainwashed her."</p>
<p>Spike laughed and Buffy promptly hit him in the face.</p>
<p>"Au!" Spike screamed and covered his nose. "Why'd you do that for?"</p>
<p>"Because what I said wasn't funny."</p>
<p>"Oh, sure, go ahead, kill the messenger because he's having fun," Spike murmured and left, angry.</p>
<p>Buffy looked at Riley.</p>
<p>"We have to find her before they do," she said and Riley nodded.</p>

<hr/>

<p>On his way back to his crypt, Spike passed the mansion. Suddenly his nostrils flared as he smelled blood. He sniffed the air and followed the scent to the mansion. He opened the door and took a deep breath to inhale the powerful scent of blood. He went deeper into the mansion and finally noticed Faith.</p>
<p>"Well, well, what have we here," he said and approached her. "Mmm, blood," he said when he noticed the pool of blood. He looked around. "Is this a self-service buffet?" he asked. There was no answer, so he approached Faith and kneeled beside her. "God, what a mess you are. Too bad I couldn't do that myself," he said and Faith jerked awake. He dipped a finger into the blood and licked it. "Mmm, delish." He frowned. "Wait a minute," he said and dipped tasted the blood again. "You're a Slayer!" he said, surprised.</p>
<p>Faith finally realized that he was a vamp and she kicked him in the face</p>
<p>"Au!" Spike said as he staggered back, clutching his nose. "Not again."</p>
<p>Faith launched herself at him, growling, and he backed off, but the chains stopped Faith.</p>
<p>"You're Faith, right, the crazy Slayer."</p>
<p>"Kill... kill... kill... I'm gonna kill you... kill you..." Faith ranted as she tried to break free of the chains.</p>
<p>"You are crazy," Spike said. "No wonder the Watchers are looking for you"</p>
<p>"Kill Watchers!" Faith screamed and threw herself at him again.</p>
<p>Spike smirked.</p>
<p>"Hmm, who to tell, Buffy or the Watchers. Decisions, decisions."</p>
<p>Faith froze when he mentioned Buffy's name and she seemed to shrink.</p>
<p>"Don't tell Buffy... Don't tell Buffy..." she said in a small voice. Then she launched at him again. "Kill you... Kill Buffy... Kill Watchers..."</p>
<p>"Lost all your marbles, have you?" Spike said, shaking his head.</p>
<p>He stared at her for a few more moments as she raved, and then left.</p>

<hr/>

<p>It took Spike a while to locate Buffy, but he finally did.</p>
<p>"What do you want now?" Buffy asked, annoyed.</p>
<p>"Hey, I'm just the messenger," Spike said and tried to stay at a safe distance.</p>
<p>"And what's the message now?"</p>
<p>"I found Faith."</p>
<p>Buffy stared at her for a few moments.</p>
<p>"You don't even know what she looks like."</p>
<p>"Well, Xander did describe her pretty well, plus the taste of her blood is unmistakable."</p>
<p>Buffy was on him in a moment. She knocked him down and straddled him.</p>
<p>"What did you do to her?" she demanded.</p>
<p>"Nothing! I mean, it was a sight to behold, but I had nothing to do with it, I swear."</p>
<p>"With what?" Buffy asked, worried.</p>
<p>"She's at the mansion looking like a steak someone didn't know how to carve properly."</p>
<p>Buffy let go of Spike and ran to the mansion. Riley followed her. Spike slowly got up and rubbed his neck.</p>
<p>"Damn Slayers, nothing but trouble," he grumbled and slowly followed them.</p>

<hr/>

<p>When she got to the mansion, Buffy stopped for a moment, nervous. The smell of blood didn't help her any. She took a deep breath and entered. The smell of blood became stronger inside, but the air was still breathable.</p>
<p>"Faith!" she called, waiting for her eyes to adjust to the darkness.</p>
<p>"Buffy?" came the weak reply.</p>
<p>Buffy started walking and soon noticed Faith. Her eyes went wide from shock and she nearly choked when she saw the condition Faith was in.</p>
<p>"God, Faith," she whispered and tears started to run down her cheeks.</p>
<p>"Buffy!" Riley called as he approached the mansion, but Buffy ignored him.</p>
<p>She approached Faith and the closer she got, the more shocked she became</p>
<p>Suddenly Faith jumped at her.</p>
<p>"Kill Buffy... kill Buffy... kill... kill..." she ranted as she tried to free the chains.</p>
<p>"Faith."</p>
<p>Faith suddenly stopped.</p>
<p>"Buffy?" she said, tears streaming down her cheeks. She sat down and pulled her legs up to her chest. "No... no... no..." she started repeating, fighting an inaudible order.</p>
<p>Buffy stepped closer.</p>
<p>"Faith..."</p>
<p>"Kill Buffy!" Faith screamed and jumped at Buffy with such ferocity that dislocated both her shoulders. She screamed in pain, but she kept trying to break free. "Kill Buffy... kill Buffy... kill... No!" she suddenly screamed and threw herself against the wall, causing more waves of pain to wash over her.</p>
<p>"Buffy?" Riley said softly when he reached her, but Buffy ignored him.</p>
<p>She stared at Faith, crying. She wanted to help her, but she didn't know how. She stepped closer and Faith suddenly attacked her again.</p>
<p>"Kill... kill... kill... kill..." she ranted.</p>
<p>Buffy then made a decision.</p>
<p>"I'm sorry, Faith," she said and knocked Faith out.</p>
<p>Faith collapsed, but Buffy caught her. She leaned her against the wall and straddled her legs, ignoring the fact that her clothes would be ruined. She observed her for a while and then caressed her.</p>
<p>As Riley observed her, he had the sinking feeling that Faith meant more to Buffy than he did.</p>
<p>Buffy then cleaned up Faith's face a bit. She took a deep breath and thought for a moment. She glanced at Riley.</p>
<p>"Hold her, Riley."</p>
<p>Riley stepped closer.</p>
<p>"What are you going to do?"</p>
<p>"I need to set her shoulders."</p>
<p>"Oh."</p>
<p>Buffy got up and Riley kneeled beside Faith and hugged her. Buffy took Faith's hand and pulled. Then she and Riley switched sides and Buffy set the other arm.</p>
<p>"See if there's a key around."</p>
<p>Riley got up and started to look around, and Buffy quickly examined Faith's wounds.</p>
<p>"I found it," Riley soon declared and returned with a key.</p>
<p>Buffy took it and unchained Faith.</p>
<p>"What a sight, isn't it?" Spike said as he casually walked in. "Makes my heart all bleeding for the past."</p>
<p>Buffy glared at him.</p>
<p>"Right now I would be very careful what I say, if I were you, especially if I had my continued existence to worry about."</p>
<p>"Okay, okay, relax," Spike said, slightly nervous.</p>
<p>Buffy picked up Faith and looked at Riley.</p>
<p>"Go to Giles and tell him we've found Faith. I'm taking her home."</p>
<p>"Are you sure?" Riley said. "I mean, I saw she was completely... insane."</p>
<p>"I'm sure."</p>
<p>"What about the Council?"</p>
<p>"I'll take Spike with me."</p>
<p>"Spike?"</p>
<p>"Me?" Spike said, surprised.</p>
<p>"Yes," Buffy said. "He can take any bullets and then I can take them out"</p>
<p>"Hey, I'm no bullet pincushion," Spike protested.</p>
<p>Buffy gave him a blank look.</p>
<p>"Wanna bet?"</p>
<p>Spike gulped.</p>
<p>"That's not fair, you know, threatening someone who can't fight back."</p>
<p>"What makes you think I care?"</p>
<p>"Bloody Slayers," Spike mumbled as Buffy walked past him.</p>

<hr/>

<p>"Trouble ahead," Spike said as they approached Buffy's house.</p>
<p>"What?"</p>
<p>"The Council. See those three?"</p>
<p>"Yes."</p>
<p>"That's them. And they've just spotted us."</p>
<p>The Council hit men started to run toward them.</p>
<p>"Here," Buffy said to Spike and turned to give him Faith.</p>
<p>"Whoa," Spike said and backed off. "I'm not taking her."</p>
<p>"Yes, you are. Unless you want me to stake you right away."</p>
<p>"On the other hand," Spike said and took Faith.</p>
<p>"Run around the block and I'll take them out."</p>
<p>"Can't I watch?"</p>
<p>"Run!"</p>
